grund completions — print a shell completion script for grund.

Usage:  grund completions <bash|zsh|fish>

The generated scripts complete subcommands and complete declared IDs for
`grund <ID>`, explicit `show`, and `grund refs <ID>` by calling the hidden helper:
`grund complete ids --prefix <word>`.

Install examples:
  source <(grund completions bash)
  grund completions zsh > ~/.zfunc/_grund
  grund completions fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/grund.fish

Exit:  0 script printed · 2 unsupported shell.
